<TITLE> BNP will act tough against graft convicts: Anwar </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 8 (bdnews24.com)  BNP supports the ongoing reform efforts and anticorruption drive and will act against the party leaders and activists convicted of corruption once indoor politics resumes, a senior leader said Friday. BNP leader and former minister MK Anwar made the remark after meeting the visiting Troika delegation of the European Union at the residence of the German ambassador in Gulshan. "The troika delegation wanted to know our position on the reform programme and antigraft drive. We have told that we support these moves of the government," he told reporters. The troika delegation asked the BNP team about where the party stands in the present political situation and the activities of the caretaker government in the one and half an hours meeting. The BNP delegation also included former foreign affairs adviser Reaz Rahman and joint secretary general Nazrul Islam Khan. Director general of the German foreign ministry's Asia and Pacific Region division Andreas Michaelis led the nine-member troika delegation. The troika delegation would meet an Awami League delegation Saturday morning. bdnew
